Basic Vulnerability Scan using Nessus Essentials
Performed a vulnerability scan on localhost using Nessus Essentials.

Summary:
Target: 127.0.0.1 (localhost)

Scan Type: Basic Network Scan

Duration: ~45 minutes

Total Vulnerabilities: 32
Critical: 0
High: 0
Medium: 2
Low: 0
Informational: 30

Key Findings:
SSL Certificate Cannot Be Trusted (Medium) — Replace with a trusted CA-issued certificate.
SMB Signing Not Required (Medium) — Enable SMB signing via Windows Group Policy.

Conclusion:
No critical or high vulnerabilities found. Remediating medium issues will enhance system security.
